headline: Why Phillips 66 (PSX) Is Up 5.0% After Beating Earnings and Launching Pipeline With Kinder Morgan
summary: In the past week, Phillips 66 reported third-quarter 2025 results with revenue of US$34.98 billion and net income of US$133 million, alongside announcing a new pipeline partnership with Kinder Morgan to transport refined products to key Western U.S. markets. Strong adjusted earnings that surpassed analyst estimates and the launch of the Western Gateway Pipeline highlight Phillips 66’s operational execution and expansion ambitions in core growth regions. headline: Are Wall Street Analysts Bullish on Kinder Morgan Stock?
summary: Kinder Morgan has lagged the broader market over the past year, yet analysts continue to see room for upside, maintaining a reasonably bullish outlook on the company’s long-term fundamentals.
